data.title: Lincolnshire parish registers places
data.text:
The Lincolnshire parish registers include baptisms, banns, marriages, and burials from across the east England county. Below we have includes lists of places found in these records organised by each life event. Each list will provide a place name and year range. The year ranges are not inclusive and may contain gaps. Many parish registers include gap years between 1649-1660. These were the years of a period of English Civil War and Commonwealth when the registering of life events in parishes was disrupted. The original parish registers are held by the Lincolnshire Archives.
